### Example 22: Matrix Times Vector

Treat a vector as a column matrix.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 0)
                             (list 0 3))))
(define v (vec/make 1 1))
(define result-vec (matrix/* A (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 1)))))
result-vec
```

<!-- BUILD: A bit awkward; ideally we'd have a helper. Prints a 2×1 matrix ((2)(3)). Or we can write a let that extracts it back to a vector. Let's refactor: -->

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 0)
                             (list 0 3))))
(define v (vec/make 1 1))
;; Convert v to column matrix, multiply, extract back
(define col (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 1))))
(define prod (matrix/* A col))
;; prod is ((2)(3)); we can read it or just print it
prod
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints ((2)(3)). -->

[VISUAL: Text output. Optionally a diagram showing the input vector and the stretched output vector.]

---

### Example 23: Determinant of a 2×2 Matrix

det(*A*) = *ad* − *bc* for *A* = [[*a*, *b*], [*c*, *d*]]. Measures area scaling.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 3 1)
                             (list 2 4))))
(matrix/determinant A)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 10 (3×4 − 1×2 = 12 − 2 = 10). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `10`. Optionally a diagram showing the unit square scaled by A into a parallelogram of area 10.]

---

### Example 24: Determinant of a 3×3 Matrix

Computed via cofactor expansion or other method.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3)
                             (list 0 1 4)
                             (list 5 6 0))))
(matrix/determinant A)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 1 (calculated via expansion). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `1`.]

---

### Example 25: Singular Matrix (Determinant Zero)

A matrix with det = 0 has no inverse.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                             (list 2 4))))
(matrix/determinant A)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 0 (rows are linearly dependent). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `0`.]

---

### Example 26: Inverse of a 2×2 Matrix

If det(*A*) ≠ 0, *A*⁻¹ exists.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 4 7)
                             (list 2 6))))
(linalg/inverse A)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints the inverse matrix (approximately ((0.6 -0.7)(-0.2 0.4)) if det=10). -->

[VISUAL: Text output of the inverse matrix.]

---

### Example 27: Verify the Inverse (A × A⁻¹ = I)

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 4 7)
                             (list 2 6))))
(define A-inv (linalg/inverse A))
(matrix/* A A-inv)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints something very close to ((1 0)(0 1)) (rounding to 3 decimals should yield I). -->

[VISUAL: Text output showing the identity matrix.]

