### Example 44: Maximum Rate of Change

The maximum rate of change is ‖∇*f*‖, achieved in the direction of ∇*f*.

```scheme
(define (f x y)
  (+ (* x x) (* y y)))

(define (grad-f x y)
  (vec/make (* 2 x) (* 2 y)))

(define grad-at-point (grad-f 3 4))
(vec/norm grad-at-point)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 10.000 (‖(6,8)‖ = √(36+64) = 10). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `10.000`.]

