### Example 47: A Three-Variable Function

*f*(*x*, *y*, *z*) = *x* + *y* + *z*. Gradient is (1, 1, 1).

```scheme
(define (f x y z)
  (+ x y z))

(define (grad-f x y z)
  (vec/make 1 1 1))

(grad-f 0 0 0)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints (vec 1 1 1). -->

[VISUAL: Text output. Conceptually, the level surfaces are planes *x* + *y* + *z* = *c*; the gradient is constant and perpendicular to these planes.]

