### Example 48: Second Partial Derivatives

∂²*f*/∂*x*² (the curvature in the *x*-direction).

```scheme
(define (f x y)
  (+ (* x x) (* y y)))

;; ∂f/∂x = 2x, so ∂²f/∂x² = 2.
(define (d2f-dx2 x y)
  2)

(d2f-dx2 3 4)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 2. -->

[VISUAL: Text output `2`.]

---

### Example 49: Mixed Partial Derivative

∂²*f*/∂*x*∂*y*. For *f* = *xy*, ∂*f*/∂*x* = *y*, ∂²*f*/∂*x*∂*y* = 1.

```scheme
(define (f x y)
  (* x y))

(define (df-dx x y)
  y)

(define (d2f-dxdy x y)
  1)

(d2f-dxdy 3 4)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints 1. -->

[VISUAL: Text output `1`.]

---

### Example 50: Clairaut's Theorem (Mixed Partials Equal)

For nice functions, ∂²*f*/∂*x*∂*y* = ∂²*f*/∂*y*∂*x*.

```scheme
(define (f x y)
  (* x x y))

;; ∂f/∂x = 2xy, ∂²f/∂x∂y = 2x.
;; ∂f/∂y = x², ∂²f/∂y∂x = 2x.
(define (d2f-dxdy x y)
  (* 2 x))

(define (d2f-dydx x y)
  (* 2 x))

(list (d2f-dxdy 3 4) (d2f-dydx 3 4))
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints (6 6), confirming equality. -->

[VISUAL: Text output `(6 6)`.]

