### Example 64: Diagonal Matrix (Easy Eigenvalues)

A diagonal matrix has eigenvalues equal to its diagonal entries.

```scheme
(define D (matrix/make (list (list 5 0)
                             (list 0 -2))))
(linalg/eigenvalues-2x2 D)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints (vec 5.000 -2.000). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `(vec 5.000 -2.000)`.]

