### Example 65: Rotation Matrix (Complex Eigenvalues, 2D Real)

A pure rotation by 90° has no real eigenvectors (every vector rotates).

*A* = [[0, -1], [1, 0]]. Eigenvalues are ±*i*.

```scheme
(define R (matrix/make (list (list 0 -1)
                             (list 1 0))))
(linalg/eigenvalues-2x2 R)
```

<!-- BUILD: May return complex eigenvalues or 'nan (depending on implementation). If eigenvalues-2x2 returns only real, it should return 'nan or (escalate 'complex ...). -->

