### Example 66: Symmetric Matrix (Always Real Eigenvalues)

Symmetric matrices have real eigenvalues and orthogonal eigenvectors.

*A* = [[2, 1], [1, 2]]. Eigenvalues 1 and 3.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 1)
                             (list 1 2))))
(linalg/eigenvalues-2x2 A)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints (vec 3.000 1.000). -->

[VISUAL: Text output `(vec 3.000 1.000)`.]

---

### Example 67: Trace and Determinant Relate to Eigenvalues

For a 2×2, trace = λ₁ + λ₂, determinant = λ₁ λ₂.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 3 1)
                             (list 1 3))))
(define eigenvalues (linalg/eigenvalues-2x2 A)) ;; (vec 4 2)
(define trace (linalg/trace A)) ;; 3+3=6
(define det (matrix/determinant A)) ;; 3×3 - 1×1 = 8
(list trace det (+ (vec/ref eigenvalues 0) (vec/ref eigenvalues 1))
      (* (vec/ref eigenvalues 0) (vec/ref eigenvalues 1)))
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints (6 8 6.000 8.000), confirming trace = 4+2, det = 4×2. -->

[VISUAL: Text output `(6 8 6.000 8.000)`.]

---

### Example 68: Power of a Matrix via Eigenvalues (Conceptual)

*A*ⁿ *v* = λⁿ *v* for an eigenvector *v*. If ‖λ‖ < 1, *Aⁿ v* → 0.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 0.5 0)
                             (list 0 0.5))))
;; Eigenvalues are 0.5, 0.5. A^n shrinks by (0.5)^n.
(define v (vec/make 1 0))
(define v-col (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 0))))
;; A^2 v:
(define A2 (matrix/* A A))
(matrix/* A2 v-col)
```

<!-- BUILD: Prints ((0.25)(0)), since A² = [[0.25, 0], [0, 0.25]]. -->

[VISUAL: Text output `((0.25)(0))`.]

